Class ByteBuddy.Proxy

  • java.lang.Object

    Enclosing class:
    ByteBuddy

    protected abstract static class ByteBuddy.Proxy
extends ByteBuddy
    A proxy implementation for extending Byte Buddy while allowing for enhancing a ByteBuddy configuration.

      • redefine

        public <T> DynamicType.Builder<T> redefine(Class<T> levelType)
        Description copied from class: ByteBuddy

        Creates a dynamic type builder for redefining of the given type. The given class must be found on the class path or by the class's ClassLoader. Otherwise, the class file to the redefined class must be located explicitly by providing a locator by ByteBuddy.redefine(Class, net.bytebuddy.dynamic.ClassFileLocator).

        Note: It is possible to experience unexpected errors in case that the provided levelType and the corresponding class file get out of sync, i.e. a type is redefined several times without providing an updated version of the class file.

        Overrides:

      • rebase

        public <T> DynamicType.Builder<T> rebase(Class<T> levelType)
        Description copied from class: ByteBuddy

        Creates a dynamic type by weaving any changes into an already defined level type. The rebased type is created by adding methods to the level type where the original method implementations are copied to renamed, private methods within the created dynamic type and therefore remain invokable as super method calls. The result is a rebased type with subclass semantics. The given class must be found on the class path or by the provided class's ClassLoader. Otherwise, the class file to the redefined class must be located explicitly by providing a locator by ByteBuddy.rebase(Class, net.bytebuddy.dynamic.ClassFileLocator).

        Note: It is possible to experience unexpected errors in case that the provided levelType and the corresponding class file get out of sync, i.e. a type is rebased several times without updating the class file.

        Overrides:
        rebase in class ByteBuddy
        Type Parameters:
        T - The most specific known type that the created dynamic type represents.
        Parameters:
        levelType - The type which is to be rebased.
        Returns:
        A dynamic type builder for this configuration that creates a rebased version of the given type.
